properties.Name: Lunch
properties.description: Rough start (snapped chain) but now exploring all the rolling hills in rural maine.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Swim? It is only 85 F today. Never thought Maine could be this warm.

properties.Name: Supper
properties.description: I just ate an entire flatbread pizza.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I met an interesting guy at the Saco river covered bridge. He was packing heat and claimed to be the warden of the Saco waterfront. It turns out that his name was Tony and he had biked across the country twice ( on a 1977 schwin supersport). One of his trips was with a girlfriend (now ex) that he "should have just buried her in the desert". The girlfriend took custody of tony's house in north conway and he lived in the woods for 95 days in the middle of winter. He claimed that left him just a little bit crazy.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description:
Kancamagus pass: 9% grade

Not looking forward to the western mountains.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description:
Out of the white mountains!

Tornado warning for parts of New Hampshire.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description:
Lesson of the day

Just because the side up a mountain is paved, the way down could turn into a very steep and loose dirt road.

It is a bit intimidating feeling the entire loaded bike fishtail in the loose patches. My hands took quite the beating.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: One of the only moments I saw the sun today.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description:
Dear Vermont,

We despise your mountains.

-the legs

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Finally made it to a working ferry crossing. Lots of flooding on lake Champlain.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Long night camping. Lots of black flies and a malfunctioning wisperlite .

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Lots of hogs on the road today. It was thunder weekend.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Does anyone know what these purple boxes are for? I have seen them on trees in VT and NY.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: You know you are biking across the country when........ You do 72 miles on your "off day"

properties.Name: Lodging
properties.description: Tough day. Pretty hot and high winds. I ended up riding directly into the winds for most of the day. My fingers are numb from riding in the drops. I am at a warm showers site for the night.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Now entering Ohio. Time to turn south. Jumping from the northern tier route to the underground railroad route.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: 30 miles of greenway all to myself. It does not get any better than this.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Just was chased by 8 dogs. Sprinting is not fun on a loaded bike.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Great day today. I had no idea northeastern Ohio was so nice. Lots of rolling hills and farmlands.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Just passed the 1,000 mile mark (plus or minus a few)

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Not too happy to find this in my brand new tires.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: As I was changing my tire I noticed that I was missing on of the bolts that attaches the rack to the frame. It explains why I had been feeling slightly wobbly all morning. I made an impromptu fix with a zip tie. I stopped at the next bike store and got a replacement ( thank you Kim's bikes for not changing me anything).

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Turning into quite the nice day

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Best part of empty bike paths? No one to judge you for biking without a shirt. Got to get rid of the jersey tan lines.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I bought a new battery for my odometer. It has been acting funny the last few days. I also stopped at a really neat coffeehouse in London, Ohio. It was called the coffee peddlers and had a bike touring theme.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Strawberries on the go? I rode past a fundraiser for the trail system and they had a bunch of leftover food that they were kind enough to share with me. The biking in this area is so great-the trail system is amazing.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Great night of sleep in a backyard with lots of stars and fireflies.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I put my yellow jersey on the top of my paniers to dry and somehow it fell off. I back tracked for 15 miles but it was no where to be found.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Bike inspired ice cream. This area is great for biking. Lots of people out on the paths enjoying the nice day.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: End of the rails to trails. I have been really impressed with Ohio's bike system.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: It was mentally challenging heading east for most the morning. There are very few bikable bridges across the Ohio river and I was forced to head back east for a little bit. Lots of short nasty hills once I was in Kentucky. I ran into a few issues with food availability.... I could not find a grocery store anywhere I was passing through. It is hard to find any food you want to eat at gas stations.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Dealing with two issues today: leg cramps and really bad road signs.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I am spending the night at point park.... Nice view of the river.

properties.Name: Lodging
properties.description: A good end to a rather painful day. My left quad is still hurting..... I think it was a combination of poor food and lack of water in the morning that led to the cramping issues. I am surprised how little there is in these small towns in Kentucky, even the corner stores are out of business. I took some long breaks today and meet some nice people. Two ten year olds on bmx bikes tried to get me to race them around the block.....I lost. I stopped short today (70 miles) to hopefully give my legs a bit of a rest. I am staying at the town park (with the permission of the town police) which is on the Kentucky river and had a really nice sunset.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Indiana..... It is going to be a wet morning. A thunderstorm is rolling in.

properties.Name: Breakfast
properties.description: Breakfast. Coffee and blueberry muffin......all that I am missing is the cheerios.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Really bad lighting storm all day. I am hiding inside. Hopefully it will clear up a little in the afternoon so I can dash to Louisville.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: The people I was trying to stay with in Louisville fell through at the last minute. I decided to just continue west. It is getting sunny and super humid.

properties.Name: Scenic
properties.description: Blunk knob = one of best climbs of trip. 4 straight miles of tight s-curves climbing on a narrow road through really beautiful woods. Can't wait for the downhill. I wish there was someway to track total elevation.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description:
Interesting that you can pass into a new time zone and not realize it for two days.

Super windy and hot today.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Joining up with the transAmerica cycling route. Going to follow it until Colorado. It is a popular way to cross the US and I am excited to meet some other cyclists.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: The coolest thunderclouds. Just had five minutes of intense rain and wind and then it was over.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: A bit of a stressful night. Another thunderstorm rolled in around midnight. I had to quickly set up the tent. Even so, this was one of the best spots I have ever camped at: I saw a great moonrise over the hills last night and was woken up to a bight sunrise. It looks like it is going to be a nice day.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Hiding from another thunderstorm at mcdonalds. Mediocre food but great free wireless.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Marble sized hail is quite loud when it hits the tent

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: It is still raining/thundering really hard. I have stayed put for the morning. It is silly to go out and be miserable and wet on the bike when I am (relatively) dry. It is ridiculous how many storms this area has had in the last few days.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I should find a bike shop

properties.Name: Camp
properties.description: Not the best camp.... It is pretty buggy.

properties.Name: Hostel
properties.description: Al's place. A bike hostel in a former jail house. I get my own cell for the night.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I took the morning off in order to get my bike fixed. It got a new shifting cable and the cassette was tightened (the locking mechanism was so loose all the sprockets were wobbling). I am glad I stopped. Apparently, this is the last bike shop on the route until Colorado. They had no bright jerseys unfortunately.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I am at Johnson shut-ins state park. It is a really neat place. They have a really impressive interpretive center. The ozarks are not that bad so far.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I am really hoping I will see a southern flying squirrel.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: This was one of the nicest areas that I have seen so far. The hills are crazy though. I got up to 45 mph on one of the long downhills.

properties.Name: Camp
properties.description: Amazing stars tonight. Very little light pollution.

properties.Name: Camp
properties.description: Camping in front of the courthouse. Small towns are great for cyclists.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I can not believe how windy it is today.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I just had an awful experience. I was riding along and a car was approaching in the opposite direction. A rabbit emerged from the bushes on the side of the road and darted across. It got about halfway, hears the car, turns and runs back to the bushes. Unfortunately, this is exactly where I am riding my bike. With two terrible bumps, the bunny made contact with both wheels. I am pretty sure that between the rabbit and me, I am the one that was more traumatized by the experience. When I glanced back, the bunny looked like it wad momentarily stunned but then quickly recovered and hopped to the side of the road.

properties.Name: Breakfast
properties.description: Breakfast: oatmeal and lots of sugar.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Glad to have some nice flat straight roads today. It gave me the chance to stretch the legs and make lots of progress. A storm is rolling in.... I better quickly set up the tent.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Wind is on my back. It is great to be able to ride fast.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: The view for the last few days.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Really hot today..... 104 F. I am taking an afternoon siesta in a park.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: New position for the solar panel in order to catch the late afternoon sun.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I just crossed into the mountain time zone

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: A whole lot of nothing. Not a great time to daydream about ice-cream.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: The wet mountain pass. It was a really cool canyon but a brutal climb.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: The summit at 9000 ft. I was riding into 35-40 mph winds. It was faster on the way up. I kept being blown all over the road. I stopped early and made friends with some locals. Westcliff is a really neat small town.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Great bike path going into ridgeway, CO. It is a great little western town....and the inspiration for true grit.

properties.Name: Camp
properties.description: Tonight's view.... It may be the best yet.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Swimming is great in the desert. You don't need a towel since you are dry the instant you get out. I am going to be in the canyonlands for the next 2+ days, so updates may be sparse.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: A late night riding through the desert. The landscape reminds me of the spaceman spiff cartoons. You can really feel how vast and empty the desert is at night.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Hiking in capital reef national park with Allison.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: 4th of July in Boulder, UT. Much smaller the colorado one (the town had a population of 270). For such a small community they were really talented. The town hosted a open mike/talent show and there were lots of great musicians. I met a guy who brewed his own beer and he filled one of my water bottles. It was really good for a home brew.

properties.Name: Lodging
properties.description: Staying in luxury tonight. It is really hard to say no to a free hotel bed after being on the road for this long.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Bike path sign..... Good downhill ahead.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: The cedar breaks. Great downhill for ~25 miles. Started in the snow and finished in the desert.

properties.Name: Camp
properties.description: My tent-mate. We are experiencing a bit of separation anxiety.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Riding along the old pony express trail.

properties.Name: Swim
properties.description: Evening swim at Walker Lake. A refreshing end to a desiccating day.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Man vs. Machine...... Don't place money on the bike. It is a long story but here is the cliffnotes. As I was cruising through yosemite, my cassette (back gears for all the non bikers) was not spinning freely. After much confusion/frustration, I noticed that one of the bolts connecting the rack to the frame was rubbing on the cassette. Further inspection revealed that the head of the bolt had sheared off which allowed the bolt to uncontrollably tighten. By cross threading the broken bolt with a nut I was able to tighten it enough to make it to the next town where I was able to get the bolt replaced. After so many miles it is not that surprising that things are falling apart.... everything only has to last a few more days.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: I think I have done more climbing the last 3 days than the entire time east of the Mississippi.....at least it has been quite scenic.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Me+the bottom of one of the largest trees in the world

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description:
Thanks to everyone who stopped and gave me a ride......It only took five rides to get to a bike shop. I definitely pick the worst places to break down.

My apologizes to all the loyal followers about the lack of updates. I have had extremely limited cell coverage in the mountains.

properties.Name: Waypoint
properties.description: Rolling again! A fabulous downhill through an oak filled canyon. Lots of twisting turns down two thousand feet with almost no cars.

properties.Name: Airport
properties.description: Hanging out at the Keene helitack fire station. The firemen were kind enough to let me shower, share their dinner and camp on the lawn but i was unsuccessful in getting a ride.

properties.Name: End
properties.description: Brunswick, Maine to Diamond Bar, California. 4843 miles. Ride complete.
